As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=2008-01-31 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> of 2010, there were 1,078 people, 491 households, and 326 families residing in the CDP. The population density was {{convert|1,714|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 100.00% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]].

The average household size was 2.19 and the average family size was 3.3.

In the CDP, the population was spread out, with 20.4% age 19 and under, 2.4% from 20 to 24, 24.1% from 25 to 44, 31% from 45 to 64, and 20.1% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 48.4 years. For every 100 females, there were 96.1 males.

The median income for a household in the CDP was $47,813, and the median income for a family was $56,932. Males had a median income of $43,333 versus $29,828 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $27,637. About 2.8% of families and 7.1% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 0.0% of those under age 18 and 4.9% of those age 65 or over.<ref>[https://archive.today/20200212213610/http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=ACS_11_5YR_DP03&prodType=table United States Census]</ref>

